--- [A] Direct run at repo root: npx ts-node scripts/seed.ts ---
This repo has src/ (product mode) and no "seed" script in package.json,
so branch 3 (product mode, no seed script) must refuse:

[seed] FAILED: product code exists but package.json defines no "seed" script — the E2E gate must not pass against an unseeded database.
(exit code 1)

This is correct behavior for this repo: verify.sh only invokes seed.ts under
--e2e when an e2e script is also defined, which this template repo does not
define. The exit-1 protects adopted repos that add product code and an e2e
script without defining seeding.

